Answer 1

Value - Piece of infomation that cannot be further reduced. Example number 1, word hello
Expression - When something can be reduced. Example number 1 plus number 2 is number 3 so this is an arithmetic expression
Variable - An identified to refer to a value which could change over time. Usually variable refers to a specific type of value : number, text or anything else
Constant - Identifier for a vlue that will not change throught the program. Example constant pi can be assigned 3.14 value which will remain the same.
Operator - A symbol that represents action that can take place on value or values. It can also work on variables since those contain values. Example +, -
Compiler - A program that converts instructions into a machine-code or lower-level form so that they can be read and executed by a computer.
Interpreter - An interpreter is a computer program that is used to directly execute program instructions written using one of the many high-level programming languages.
Operating system - The software that supports a computer's basic functions, such as scheduling tasks, executing applications, and controlling peripherals.
String -  Most languages have a data type called a string, which is used for data values that are made up of ordered sequences of characters, such as "hello world".
Boolean - Boolean data type is a data type that has one of two possible values (usually denoted true and false) which is intended to represent the two truth values of logic and Boolean algebra.


