Answer 3

Code:
# Python program to swap two variables

x = 2
y = 3

print('Value of x before swapping:', x)
print('Value of y before swapping:', y)

# create a temporary variable and swap the values
temp = x
x = y
y = temp

print('Value of x after swapping:', x)
print('Value of y after swapping:', y)


Explanation - This program swaps 2 variables x and y with each others values. In the example before swapping x and y had values of 2 and 3 respectively but after swapping the values are 3 and 2 respectively for x and y.
This was one of the examples provided in the lecture 2. Found the code at https://www.programiz.com/python-programming/examples/swap-variables and modified a bit to better undserstand it.


Code execution:
C:\Users\sghosh\Documents\ucsd_python>python swap.py
Value of x before swapping: 2
Value of y before swapping: 3
Value of x after swapping: 3
Value of y after swapping: 2
